body:
*Repro steps*:

1. Create a new Flutter project in IJ
1. Delete `new Text(
          'Button tapped $_counter time${ _counter == 1 ? '' : 's' }.',
        )` in line 80
1. Type `new Pad` and complete to Padding

*Expected result*: Editor completes:
```
child:
```
 to:
```
child: new Padding(
  padding: ,
),
```
thus making it clear that a `padding` argument is required.

*Actual result*: Editor completes to just `new Padding()`

comment_data.body: This feature sounds like a great carrot to encourage dart package authors (and flutter framework authors) to annotate @required correctly. :)
Not sure if there's an is an issue for the associated quick-fix for this -
> Not sure if there's an is an issue for the associated quick-fix for this - Quick-fixes landed last week. ü§ò Hope to dig into completions this week.

A little refinement to the proposal.

Instead of:

```dart
child: new Padding(
  padding: ,
),
```

I think we want:


```dart
child: new Padding(
  padding: null,
),
```

since it will parse cleanly.

That sounds right. And then the Flutter framework should be updated to mark child `@required` so that the expansion becomes:

```dart
   child: new Padding(
     padding: null,
     child: null,
   ),
```

As of https://github.com/dart-lang/sdk/commit/cc0036d5ad46793b9399443f4d62e3a4c1680320, support is in place on the DAS side.  Once https://github.com/JetBrains/intellij-plugins/pull/495 lands, completions in IDEA will go from a proposal like this

![screen shot 2017-03-02 at 1 13 05 pm](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/67586/23527253/10700cf0-ff4a-11e6-94e8-cb39057a8bc3.png)

to generated code like this

![screen shot 2017-03-02 at 1 13 17 pm](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/67586/23527254/10706e0c-ff4a-11e6-9ceb-d5924d1f3dd2.png)

(Note that `x`, `y` and `null` are linked edits and you can TAB between them.)

FYI @sethladd
